Class AbstractAludraService

java.lang.Object

public abstract class AbstractAludraService
extends Object
implements AludraService

Abstract parent class for custom AludraService implementations. It provides the features which are usually implemented equally among different services: Handling of context, test case and system connector.

Author:
Volker Bergmann

Method Detail

init

public final void init(AludraServiceContext context)
Implements the init() method. Stores the context parameter in the aludraServiceContext field which can be accessed by subclasses. Extracts the test case log object from the context object and stores it in the #testCaseLog field which also can be accessed by subclasses. Afterwards, initService() is called.

Specified by:
init in interface AludraService
Parameters:
context - Service context which can be used to access other services

getInstanceName

public String getInstanceName()
Description copied from interface: AludraService
Returns the instance name which applies to this service instance. Could be null in some cases (for some service types), so be careful to handle this case.

Specified by:
getInstanceName in interface AludraService
Returns:
The instance name which applies to this service instance, or null if not set.

initService

public abstract void initService()
Abstract initialization method to be implemented by child classes for individual initialization operations. Implementors can access the protected aludraServiceContext field to retrieve instances of other services, if required.
